          description:
            "🏙️ Tucked away between the skyscrapers, hospital, and university at Amsterdam's business district Zuid, you'll find the most peaceful surprise: the Botanical Garden Zuidas. Although relatively small, you can still get that sense of being lost in nature with all its narrow winding paths and hidden corners. A real photographer's paradise with its special Chinese Penjin garden, a unique bonsai array, and the Netherlands' largest cacti and succulents collection.\n\n📷 Photography tips:\n• Explore small paths to discover hidden corners with interesting plants and flowers.\n• Sit in the Penjin Garden and soak in its visual atmosphere.\n• Visit the greenhouses for the impressive cactus collection.\n• Find succulents behind the greenhouse.\n• Use the surrounding water as a lovely backdrop.\n\n🌱 Established in 1967 to support students and researchers, the garden is a unique blend of nature and urban life. It offers a bench to quietly enjoy nature around every corner. Sitting among the greenery, you'll often see intriguing visual combinations like a palm tree swaying with an office building in the background.",
