          description:
            "🏞️ From wildflowers to a tango concert, I visited this restored 1920s garden near Oosterbeek. It offers an interesting blend of formal structure and wild charm. Nestled between the forests, Tuin de Lage Oorsprong is a hidden gem with varied landscapes. With its walled garden layout, it provides a sense of intimacy while offering many photographic opportunities.\n\n📷 Photography tips:\n• Capture the geometric patterns of the formal beds from the elevated walkway.\n• Use the old brick walls or orangery as a backdrop for flower close-ups.\n• Don't miss the greenhouse for some atmospheric shots.\n• Explore the wild garden area for more natural compositions and insect shots.\n• Visit during different seasons for varied color palettes and moods.\n\n🌱 Originally part of a country estate, this garden was heavily damaged during World War 2 and fell into disrepair. It was lovingly restored by volunteers. Today, it's a living museum of garden design and sculptures, showcasing both historical elements and modern sustainable gardening practices. It's also the festive site of many concerts and weddings.\n\n✅ Visiting Tips: \n• Enjoy garden concerts at the natural amphitheater every Sunday.\n• Enjoy a cup of tea or coffee at the charming orangery.\n• Easily accessible by car or bike from Arnhem.",
