          preview:
            "🏞️ From the oldest tree of Amsterdam to an edible garden, ARTIS isn't just a zoo - recently it officially became a botanical garden as well! With over 700…",
          description:
            "🏞️ From the oldest tree of Amsterdam to an edible garden, ARTIS isn't just a zoo - recently it officially became a botanical garden as well! With over 700 trees from 200+ species, this urban oasis offers a unique blend of animal and plant life. As the newest member of the Dutch Association of Botanical Gardens, ARTIS is an unexpected floral paradise for photography.\n\n📷 Photography tips:\n• Capture the Heijmans oak, Amsterdam's oldest tree.\n• Visit the tropical greenhouse for butterfly photography.\n• Use the charming historical buildings and bridges as backdrops for your photos.\n• Look for the extensive bee and insect garden to observe some buzzing friends.\n• Explore the themed gardens for diverse compositions - from Japanese to edible plants.\n\n🌱 ARTIS isn't just preserving history; it's actively supporting urban biodiversity. With year-round blooming flowers, it's a crucial food source for city-dwelling insects and bees. You'll also see an extensive population of city herons who have comfortably made it their home. The edible gardens provide food for the zoo's herbivores - a great example of sustainable practices in action.\n\n✅ Visiting Tips:\n• Open year-round (check website for current hours).\n• Join a guided tour to learn more about the rare plant species.\n• Visit the Stek for insights into houseplant care.\n• Easily accessible by public transport in central Amsterdam, walking distance from subway station Weesperplein.\n• I",
