          preview:
            "Ever dreamed of wandering through a kaleidoscope of garden styles? Welcome to Bloemenpark Appeltern, a photographer's dream and one of my top picks to visit in…",
          description:
            "🌸 Ever dreamed of wandering through a kaleidoscope of garden styles? I first came here as a child, when my parents visited for garden inspiration, and it stayed with me for years — the feeling of a theme park, but made entirely of gardens. Every corner hid something new to discover.\n\n🌿 When I came back as an adult, camera in hand and a friend alongside me, I fell in love with it all over again. We spent full sweltering summer days here, completely lost in it. Even on the hottest visits, the sound of trickling water was never far away — fountains, little streams, the gentle movement of water threading through the gardens. It was cooling just to hear it.\n\n📷 Photography tips:\n• Look for shadow patterns cast by foliage onto garden walls on sunny days — the light does extraordinary things here.\n• Walls with windows and doorways built into them create natural frames worth hunting for.\n• Don't walk past the ponds without stopping — the reflections are some of the best shots in the park.\n• Experiment with macro on the flowers and insects, there is never a shortage of either.\n\n🏡 Why is it a must visit?\n• Showcases countless garden designs and landscaping styles\n• Bursting with vibrant flowers and wildlife\n• Endless photo opportunities around every corner\n• Restaurants on site for coffee, apple pie and lunch",
